	"version": "636",
	"class": "vulnerability",
	"metadata": {
		"title": "net: http: Denial of service due to improper 100-continue handling in net/http (moderate)",
		"reference": [
			{
				"ref_id": "CVE-2024-24791",
				"ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-24791",
				"source": "CVE"
			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: The MITRE CVE dictionary describes this issue as: The net/http HTTP/1.1 client mishandled the case where a server responds to a request with an \"Expect: 100-continue\" header with a non-informational (200 or higher) status. This mishandling could leave a client connection in an invalid state, where the next request sent on the connection will fail. An attacker sending a request to a net/http/httputil.ReverseProxy proxy can exploit this mishandling to cause a denial of service by sending \"Expect: 100-continue\" requests which elicit a non-informational response from the backend. Each such request leaves the proxy with an invalid connection, and causes one subsequent request using that connection to fail.",
